text.tspan: Incidents of conflict and one-sided violence since 1989, 1989 to 2016
The data refer to direct violent deaths. Deaths due to disease or famine caused by conflict are excluded.
Extra-judicial killings in custody are also excluded. Only incidents involving more than 25 deaths are included.
One-sided violence is that between a named organization and civilians, such as genocides. The spike in 1994
reflects the high death toll of the Rwandan genocide.
